CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 26, 1958, pg. A3 reads: "Homewood-Brushton "Y" Board - Volunteering their time, energies and finances to the building fund goal of $40,000 is the Homewood-Brushton YMCA integrated board of management shown in above picture. Seated in the front row, left to right: G.W. McCreery, Dr. C.B. Alster, Dr. H. Lee Briney, Charles L. Blynn, Atty. Lynn Washington, Edward McFeathers, the Rev. J.W. Findley Brown and Samuel T. Bowler.  Back row: C.E. Askew, Robert W. Smith, W.T. Pitzer, chairman; the Rev. J.A. Williams, Robert W. Woodruff, Charles T. Beckett and Thomas Madden.  The drive opened April 20 ad closes May 31. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Homewood-Brushton YMCA management board, seated, left to right: G.W. McCreery, Dr. C.B. Alster, Dr. H. Lee Briney, Charles L. Blynn, Atty. Lynn Washington, Edward McFeathers, Rev. J.W. Findley Brown, and Samuel T. Bowler, and Thomas Madden; standing, left to right: two unknown, Charles T. Beckett, unknown, C.E. Askew, Rev. J.A. Williams, Robert W. Smith, W.T. Pitzer, unknown, Robert W. Woodruff, and two unknown, gathered around banquet table
